\begin_layout Section
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Model and Treatments
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We closely follow the model of 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Dellavigna2018"

\end_inset

 for the worker side and modify it to incorporate the possibility of discriminat
ion from the worker side.
 Assuming risk neutrality, a worker 
\begin_inset Formula $i\in\left\{ B,W\right\} $
\end_inset

 solves the following problem when working for an employer 
\begin_inset Formula $j\in\left\{ U,B,W\right\} $
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $W$
\end_inset

 denote the unknown, black or white race of an agent (employer or worker)
 respectively;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\underbrace{max}_{e_{ij}\geq0}U_{ij}=\underbrace{max}_{e_{ij}\geq0}\left(F+(s_{i}+\rho_{ij}\mathbbm{1}_{Gift}+\alpha_{ij}v_{j}+p)e_{ij}-c(e_{ij})\right)\label{eq:utility}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $e_{ij}$
\end_inset

 is the number of points (on a button-pressing task) scored by worker 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 when working for an employer 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $F$
\end_inset

 is the fixed money paid for participating in the experiment, 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{i}$
\end_inset

 captures the sense of duty, norm, intrinsic motivation, and competitiveness
 of worker towards the task which is independent of the employer.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho_{ij}$
\end_inset

 is the reciprocity parameter per unit of effort which is kicked in whenever
 an employer 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

 awards gift to the worker 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
`a
\end_layout

\end_inset

 la 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Gneezy2006"

\end_inset

.
 
\family roman
\series medium
\shape up
\size normal
\emph off
\bar no
\strikeout off
\uuline off
\uwave off
\noun off
\color none

\begin_inset Formula $\mathbbm{1}_{Gift}$
\end_inset


\family default
\series default
\shape default
\size default
\emph default
\bar default
\strikeout default
\uuline default
\uwave default
\noun default
\color inherit
 is an indicator function which assumes a value 
\begin_inset Formula $1$
\end_inset

 when a gift is rewarded by the employer, 
\begin_inset Formula $0$
\end_inset

 otherwise.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{ij}$
\end_inset

 captures the altruistic preference of worker 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 towards employer 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

 per unit of effort 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
`a
\end_layout

\end_inset

 la 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Becker1974"

\end_inset

 given that 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{j}$
\end_inset

 is the value of the unit of effort to the employer 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 is the piece rate per unit of effort.
 
\begin_inset Formula $c(e_{ij})$
\end_inset

 is the cost of effort, which is assumed to be the same for all workers
 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

.
 We assume the regularity conditions 
\begin_inset Formula $c'()>0$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $c''()>0$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $lim_{e\rightarrow\infty}c'(e)=\infty.$
\end_inset

 
